Starting a healthy diet can be a challenge, but it is possible to make small changes that can have a big impact. Here are some tips to get you started:

2. Make sure to eat a variety of foods, including fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean proteins, and healthy fats.
3. Limit your intake of processed foods and added sugars.
4. Drink plenty of water to stay hydrated.
5. Eat breakfast every day to help keep your energy levels up.
6. Eat smaller portions and eat more slowly to help you feel fuller longer.
7. Make sure to get enough sleep and exercise to help keep your energy levels up.
8. Keep track of your progress and reward yourself for your successes.</s>
